14/09/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Tuesday (13 September) that they have smashed an international channel smuggling illegal immigrants from Asia to Western Europe. Officials say four Greeks and one German were detained after a large-scale surveillance operation was conducted in co-operation with German authorities. Police continue searching for four other suspects. 
In other news, the Macedonian Interior Ministry reported on Tuesday that police detained a group of Albanian nationals attempting to illegally enter Greece from Macedonia at the Star Dojran border crossing. The eight allegedly were hidden in a vehicle driven by a Macedonian citizen. (Kathimerini - 14/09/05; A1 TV - 13/09/05)
